    {
      "id": "VVpcO20bMVQwdPiNxVLAI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1007.750055222285,
      "y": 5796.432757423036,
      "width": 617.5396728515625,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1h",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 772933753,
      "version": 385,
      "versionNonce": 1429493881,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783521906299,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Cons\n1) CDN is costly so store only those url which have fixed\ncriteria or query parameter.\n2) Even if Redis Global counter is memcache, still need one n/w\ncall\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Cons\n1) CDN is costly so store only those url which have fixed\ncriteria or query parameter.\n2) Even if Redis Global counter is memcache, still need one n/w\ncall\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Yg4XpVPvn05GpTycprc1v",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -152.24994477771497,
      "y": 6249.28990028018,
      "width": 1803.5789794921875,
      "height": 725,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1i",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 243214809,
      "version": 2410,
      "versionNonce": 1277302967,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783522538461,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Possible Scenario\n1) If DB down just before insert tinyUrl mapping ?\n2) If Global counter down just before random number generate ?\n3) memory issue in CDN as no old url got exclude or removed ? how and what strategy you can use for it ?\n4) Service down just before passed data to CDN ?\n\nSolution\n1) If DB down just before insert tinyUrl Mapping ?\n-> Even if DB is down we have master slave system so any slave can take place of it.\n->One more solution and use to reduce db call for each and every tinyUrl mapping entry. so store in redis cache with same master slave replica and on fixed interval or number of entries\ndo batch wise insert into db. same question what happen if redis crased before insert into db or replica of redis.\n\n2) Global counter down just before random number generate?\n--> master slave pattern we can use and along with it will store global counter value at fixed interval into db for tracking purpose.\n--> instead of storing fix global counter, we will store counter value along with tinyUrk entries , so whenver it is down and come up, read from db what will be counter number \nlatest entry has\n\n3) Memory issue in CDN?\n--> We need to remove entries on fixed interval from CDN, based on their status means if URL not used from last 3 years need to remove from cdn and cache.\n--> For this we need to either run corn job at fixed interval. if 1M url got expired means not used what you will do at that time to remove from cdn.\n--> Two approach\n  1) regular interval we need to update or remove url mapping from CDN.\n  2) When URL called change their status or interval time. so after fixed interval we call cdn for update url it will remove all url whose status got changed to expired or interval got\nelipsed.\n \n4) service down before passed data to CDN\n-> No worries for fixed interval we already running cron job to which update that entry.\n\n ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Possible Scenario\n1) If DB down just before insert tinyUrl mapping ?\n2) If Global counter down just before random number generate ?\n3) memory issue in CDN as no old url got exclude or removed ? how and what strategy you can use for it ?\n4) Service down just before passed data to CDN ?\n\nSolution\n1) If DB down just before insert tinyUrl Mapping ?\n-> Even if DB is down we have master slave system so any slave can take place of it.\n->One more solution and use to reduce db call for each and every tinyUrl mapping entry. so store in redis cache with same master slave replica and on fixed interval or number of entries\ndo batch wise insert into db. same question what happen if redis crased before insert into db or replica of redis.\n\n2) Global counter down just before random number generate?\n--> master slave pattern we can use and along with it will store global counter value at fixed interval into db for tracking purpose.\n--> instead of storing fix global counter, we will store counter value along with tinyUrk entries , so whenver it is down and come up, read from db what will be counter number \nlatest entry has\n\n3) Memory issue in CDN?\n--> We need to remove entries on fixed interval from CDN, based on their status means if URL not used from last 3 years need to remove from cdn and cache.\n--> For this we need to either run corn job at fixed interval. if 1M url got expired means not used what you will do at that time to remove from cdn.\n--> Two approach\n  1) regular interval we need to update or remove url mapping from CDN.\n  2) When URL called change their status or interval time. so after fixed interval we call cdn for update url it will remove all url whose status got changed to expired or interval got\nelipsed.\n \n4) service down before passed data to CDN\n-> No worries for fixed interval we already running cron job to which update that entry.\n\n ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
